  "text": "The Envoy stats system in v1.31.2 is implemented across multiple C++ source files organized by functional area:\n\n## Stats Scope Hierarchy\nThe Stats::Scope hierarchy is defined in envoy/stats/scope.h with the base Scope interface. Implementations include:\n- ThreadLocalStoreImpl::ScopeImpl (source/common/stats/thread_local_store.h) - Thread-local scopes for per-thread stat management\n- IsolatedScopeImpl (source/common/stats/isolated_store_impl.h) - Single-threaded isolated scopes\n\n## Symbol Table and StatNamePool\nThe symbol table manages efficient stat name interning:\n- source/common/stats/symbol_table.h/cc - SymbolTable implementation with StatNamePool for pooled allocation of stat names\n- Provides memory-efficient storage for frequently-accessed stat name strings\n\n## Tag Extraction and Tag Producers\nTag extraction from metric names is handled by:\n- source/common/stats/tag_extractor_impl.h/cc - TagExtractor implementation for extracting tags from stat names\n- source/common/stats/tag_producer_impl.h/cc - TagProducerImpl for managing tag extraction rules\n- source/common/stats/tag_utility.h/cc - Utility functions for tag processing\n\n## Core Stats Allocators and Implementations\n- source/common/stats/allocator_impl.h/cc - AllocatorImpl for creating and managing stat objects (counters, gauges, histograms)\n- source/common/stats/thread_local_store.h/cc - ThreadLocalStoreImpl, the main thread-local store implementation\n- source/common/stats/isolated_store_impl.h/cc - IsolatedStoreImpl for non-thread-safe stat stores\n- source/common/stats/metric_impl.h/cc - MetricImpl template base for counter, gauge, and text readout implementations\n- source/common/stats/histogram_impl.h/cc - HistogramImpl and ThreadLocalHistogramImpl for histogram statistics\n\n## Null Implementations (No-op stats)\n- source/common/stats/null_counter.h - NullCounterImpl\n- source/common/stats/null_gauge.h - NullGaugeImpl\n- source/common/stats/null_text_readout.h - NullTextReadoutImpl\n\n## Stats Filtering and Matching\n- source/common/stats/stats_matcher_impl.h/cc - StatsMatcherImpl for filtering which stats are tracked\n\n## Custom Stat Namespaces\n- source/common/stats/custom_stat_namespaces_impl.h/cc - CustomStatNamespacesImpl for namespace configuration\n- envoy/stats/custom_stat_namespaces.h - Interface definition\n\n## Prometheus Stats Formatting and Dispatch\n- source/server/admin/prometheus_stats.h/cc - PrometheusStatsFormatter for formatting metrics in Prometheus exposition format\n\n## Stat Sinks - Metric Dispatch\nMetrics are dispatched to various sinks:\n\n**Statsd-based sinks:**\n- source/extensions/stat_sinks/common/statsd/statsd.h/cc - Core Statsd implementation\n- source/extensions/stat_sinks/common/statsd/tag_formats.h/cc - Tag formatting for statsd protocols\n- source/extensions/stat_sinks/statsd/config.h/cc - Standard statsd sink configuration\n- source/extensions/stat_sinks/dog_statsd/config.h/cc - Datadog statsd variant\n- source/extensions/stat_sinks/graphite_statsd/config.h/cc - Graphite statsd variant\n\n**Other metric sinks:**\n- source/extensions/stat_sinks/hystrix/config.h/cc and hystrix.h/cc - Hystrix metrics sink\n- source/extensions/stat_sinks/metrics_service/config.h/cc - gRPC metrics service sink\n- source/extensions/stat_sinks/metrics_service/grpc_metrics_service_impl.h/cc - gRPC service implementation\n- source/extensions/stat_sinks/metrics_service/grpc_metrics_proto_descriptors.h/cc - Prometheus proto descriptors\n- source/extensions/stat_sinks/open_telemetry/config.h/cc - OpenTelemetry metrics sink\n- source/extensions/stat_sinks/open_telemetry/open_telemetry_impl.h/cc - OpenTelemetry implementation\n- source/extensions/stat_sinks/open_telemetry/open_telemetry_proto_descriptors.h/cc - OpenTelemetry proto descriptors\n- source/extensions/stat_sinks/wasm/config.h/cc and wasm_stat_sink_impl.h - WebAssembly-based sink\n\n## Supporting Utilities\n- source/common/stats/utility.h/cc - General stats utilities\n- source/common/stats/stat_merger.h/cc - Stat merging utilities\n- source/common/stats/timespan_impl.h/cc - Timespan tracking for latency metrics\n- source/common/stats/recent_lookups.h/cc - Tracking of recently accessed stats\n- source/common/stats/deferred_creation.h - Deferred stat creation utilities\n\n## Interface Headers\n- envoy/stats/store.h - StoreRoot interface\n- envoy/stats/sink.h - Sink interface for metric backends\n- envoy/stats/allocator.h - Allocator interface\n- envoy/stats/tag.h - Tag definitions\n- envoy/stats/tag_extractor.h - Tag extraction interface\n- envoy/stats/tag_producer.h - Tag producer interface\n- envoy/stats/stats_matcher.h - Stats filtering interface\n\nThe architecture uses a hierarchical approach with scopes containing stats, symbol tables for efficient name storage, tag extractors that parse metric names for labels, and a sink dispatch system that publishes metrics to various backends (Prometheus, statsd, gRPC services, OpenTelemetry, etc.)."
